# Exclude all copied client files except the two hand-patched model files.
# The local-patches/ tree is a temporary workaround until the datadog-api-spec
# change (OPA-5637) is merged and datadog-api-client-go is regenerated.
#
# To keep the commit small, we only track the two patched Go source files plus
# the go.mod / go.sum needed for `replace` to resolve.

# Ignore everything by default
*

# Allow the patched model files
!datadog-api-client-go/
!datadog-api-client-go/v2/
!datadog-api-client-go/v2/api/
!datadog-api-client-go/v2/api/datadogV2/
!datadog-api-client-go/v2/api/datadogV2/model_observability_pipeline_amazon_s3_generic_destination.go
!datadog-api-client-go/v2/api/datadogV2/model_observability_pipeline_amazon_s3_destination_server_side_encryption.go

# Allow the module metadata needed by the replace directive
!datadog-api-client-go/v2/go.mod
!datadog-api-client-go/v2/go.sum

# Allow this .gitignore itself
!.gitignore
